### What what surprised you when you tested it: 
What surprised me most during testing was how confidently the model could imitate camera-angle vocabulary while still failing to preserve the deeper spatial logic of the scene. For example, the model often produced outputs that looked visually convincing at first glance, but object proportions, depth, visibility, and textures would gradually become inconsistent when the viewpoint changed more dramatically. I realized that lightweight image-editing models are not truly “understanding” 3D space — they are estimating or inventing hidden spatial information that was never present in the original image. This became an important turning point in my research because it changed the project from “finding a better model” into building a system for testing perspective reasoning itself. 

